ters c.20 mm high, but of uneven height), to a maximum length of 52 cm.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":762,"dimensions":763}," The letters show some irregularity, with fairly pronounced serifs, and lengthy tails to the letter R. The first two words are separated from the rest by a space; an interpunct is visible at the end of the dedicant’s name, and the final abbreviated phrase is separated from the rest by a large hedera (ivy leaf). The letter I in line 1 is frequently taller than the rest (but so too is the first L in line 1); the final I of line 1 is somewhat irregularly carved.",[764,766,768],{"type":130,"l":131,"from":132,"to":132,"h":765,"unit":134},"18-25",{"type":130,"l":325,"from":137,"to":137,"h":767,"unit":134},"19-23",{"type":141,"l":336,"from":132,"to":137,"h":769,"unit":134},"7-15",{"_":771,"notBefore":772,"notAfter":773,"evidence":562},"Statue can be dated stylistically to the late Antonine period (i.e. the 180s or 190s CE), and the text is compatible with such a date.",180,199,[775,776],{"_":152,"type":153,"ref":154},{"_":156,"type":157,"ref":158,"offset":159},[778],[162,163],[780,781],37.998037,14.262643,{"_":170,"role":171,"ref":172},{"_":784,"type":175},"ME 20194",{"_":276,"mainLang":277,"languages":786},[276],"175724",{"n":182,"url":789,"height":790,"width":791,"desc":366,"surfaceType":187},"ISic000804_tiled.tif","1949px","4512px",[],[190,192,287,794,289,198,200],"Scibona, 2008, Statuary",[202,204,291,796,293,210,212],"EQC3W4UU",[798,799,800,237,754,245,218,219,220,221,218,222,298,277],"isic000804","dedication of a statue to ceres, by iulius acilius hermes, sevir",{"_":10},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Cereri sacr(um) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> Iulius Acilius Her-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>mes · pro honor(e) seviratus ❦ d(eae) d(onum) d(edit) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":226,"date":3,"citedRange":803,"ptr":804,"ref":805,"title":2,"citation":4},"19 no.9 fig.1-2",{"target":229},{"_":231,"target":231},{"file":807,"uri":807,"title":808,"status":809,"editionAuthor":11,"type":810,"objectType":811,"material":812,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":814,"handNote":817,"date":824,"places":828,"geo":831,"provenance":152,"provenanceGeo":833,"country":167,"region":168,"settlement":152,"repository":836,"idno":837,"textLang":839,"tmNumber":841,"facsimile":842,"letterHeights":845,"publications":846,"zotero":847,"keywords":848,"html":852,"bibl":853},"ISic000805","Fragmentary latin inscription mentioning a proconsul",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":310,"ana":311,"ref":312},{"_":813,"ana":246,"ref":247},"marble (pink)",{"layout":815},{"rs":816,"damage":24},{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":818,"dimensions":819},"Letters are 50mm high, tall, thin, serifed. P and R are open; the hastae of M join early and extend upwards; a hedera like interpunct (tail top and bottom to a hollow element) appears once between C and V of line 2.",[820,823],{"type":130,"l":821,"from":132,"to":329,"h":822,"unit":134},"Line 1-3","50",{"type":141,"l":258,"from":132,"to":137,"unit":134},{"_":825,"notBefore":826,"notAfter":827,"precision":149},"3rd century CE",201,300,[829,830],{"_":152,"type":153,"ref":154},{"_":156,"type":157,"ref":158,"offset":159},[832],[162,163],[834,835],37.998054,14.262639,{"_":170,"role":171,"ref":172},{"_":838,"type":175},"ME 20228",{"_":276,"mainLang":277,"languages":840},[276],"175725",{"n":182,"url":843,"height":844,"width":634,"desc":635,"surfaceType":187},"ISic000805_tiled.tif","5256px",[],[190,192,287,195,196,198,200],[202,204,291,207,208,210,212],[849,850,851,13,310,813,218,219,220,221,218,222,298,277],"isic000805","fragmentary latin inscription mentioning a proconsul",{"_":10},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\